SEW SEWING

Sew (Trade ability)
Command:  sew [number] <item>
          sew info <item>

The art of sewing is one of the oldest and simplest trade skills, but it also
makes some of the finest clothing and the lightest armor. The primary resources
required for sewing are skins or cloth. The Master Tailor ability will allow
you to sew faster, as will sewing in a tailor shop.

For a list of clothing items you can sew, see HELP CLOTHING.

With basic Sewing, you can make:
  whip -- primitive weapon
  canteen -- holds drinks
  satchel -- increases carrying capacity
  tent -- a portable shelter
  sail -- for shipbuilding

Additional sewing items are available from other abilities in the Trade skill,
as well as patterns and crafts hidden around the world.

See also: CRAFT INFO, CRAFTING LEVEL, RESOURCES, KEEP, LEATHERWORKING,
   RAWHIDE STITCHING, RECIPES, MASTER TAILOR
#
SHIP SHIPS 

(Disambiguation: Did you mean HELP SHIP COMMAND ?)

The most efficient form of ocean travel, ships can be sailed at a fixed speed
(with 'sail <direction>'), consuming no moves.

Ships can be used to manually transport resources, but items inside a ship's
storage hold (via 'put <item> [in] <ship>') will auto-store to the empire's
main island if the ship is left alone at sea.

Ships can also be used to transport resources automatically using the ship
command.

See also: BOARD, DISEMBARK, SAIL, SHIPBUILDING, SHIPPING, DISPATCH
